w God, and an artist citing the Quran and using metal gears and chains to celebrate the diversity of the pilgrims who come to Mecca.Crossing the Kingdom paints a lucid portrait of contemporary Saudi culture and the lives of individuals, who like us all grapple with modernity at the dawn of the twenty-first century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  a20th century.  a21st century.  aancient cities.  aancient ruins.  acamel.  acontemporary.  acurrent affairs.  adesert.  aforeign country.  aimmigrants.  aimmigration.  ajeddah.  akingdom.  alaw and order.  amiddle east.  amiddle eastern culture.  amodern world.  amuslim world.  amuslim.  anatural resources.  anatural world.  aoil.  aoppressed women.  apersian gulf.  apersonal narrative.  aprisons.  aprotest.  ared sea.  asaudi arabia.  asaudi culture.  asocial science.  asufi.  atravel memoir.  atravel.  atraveler.  atrue story.  awomens rights.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831106675470 cprintz978052029027340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096451840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520964518423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520964518/original  a978-3-11-066754-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY